# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — Files & Folders Excluded from Git Version Control
# =============================================================================
# Any file or pattern listed here will be IGNORED by Git — it won't be
# tracked, committed, or pushed to GitHub. This is critical for keeping
# sensitive data (passwords, tokens, API keys) out of public repositories.
# =============================================================================

# Ignore the .env file because it contains the Docker Hub access token
# (DOCKERTOKEN). If this token were pushed to a public GitHub repo, anyone
# could use it to push/pull images to your Docker Hub account.
# Instead, we store it as a GitHub Actions SECRET (Settings → Secrets)
# so the CI/CD pipeline can use it without exposing it in code.
.env
